      "title": "Plot Twist: How the $110B Paramount-Warner Deal Rewrites Media",
      "summary": "The DOJ's approval of Paramount Skydance's $110.9 billion acquisition of Warner Bros. Discovery without requiring asset spin-offs signals a major shift in media consolidation policy. This decision removes the regulatory ceiling that has suppressed legacy media valuations and creates a 14% merger arbitrage spread in WBD stock. The deal reflects the streaming industry's need for premium content libraries and positions legacy studios for defensive consolidation, though both companies face margin compression challenges from the shift to streaming.",
